{
  "_comment": "Register person-GUIDs that must NOT share a slug with a same-named peer. The officials slug is slugify(name, institution), which is unique only while `institution` names a specific body. For much of the register it does not — 2,538 declarants sit under the group label 'Училища', 1,712 under 'Детски градини', 978 under 'Процедури по ЗОП' — so two different people with the same legal name in the same group collapse onto one slug, and their filings merge into one profile that publishes neither person's wealth correctly. Every GUID listed here is re-slugged with the GUID folded into the disambiguator, which separates it from the peer that keeps the bare slug. Keyed on the GUID rather than the slug because the GUID is the register's own per-person identity and is stable across a declarant's filings (verified: 9,893 of 9,954 multi-year declarants keep one GUID). Same discipline as scripts/officials/_aliases.json: an explicit, reviewable table rather than a heuristic. scripts/officials/index.ts warns loudly when it meets a collision that is NOT listed here, so a new one surfaces on the next ingest instead of silently merging.",
  "_howToAdd": "Run the ingest; any 'slug collision' warning names the slug and the competing GUIDs. Add the SECOND and subsequent GUIDs (leave one out — that person keeps the bare slug) and re-run.",
